[[div class="blockquote"]]
= [[size 150%]]**SCP-8426 Ontological Analysis**[[/size]]
Using the information gained through physical analysis, and with the understanding that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]information gathered based on perception had increased unreliability[[/span]], investigation attempted to analyze SCP-8426 in alternative ways. Due to the  [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]ontological nature of the anomaly impacting SCP-8426[[/span]], investigation elected to utilize both Semantic and Ontological analysis to identify the core 'ideas' associated with SCP-8426.

-----

**Semantic Composition:** A significant issue in understanding SCP-8426 has been the ontological redefinition event; due to this, our understanding of the conceptual nature of SCP-8426 is limited to the fact that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426 is not a weapon[[/span]]. To understand what SCP-8426 //is//, we analyzed the semantic composition of SCP-8426 via Noospheric mapping and direct ontological comparison. The following concepts are presented, based on their ontological overlap with SCP-8426:
* Innovation: [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is unpredictable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoRand A"]]17%[[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoRand B"]]80%[[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoRand C"]]60.2%[[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoRand D"]]0.1%[[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoRand E"]]44%[[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoRand F"]]30%[[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoRand G"]]0%[[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoRand H"]]-20%[[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoRand I"]]7%[[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoRand J"]]25%[[/span]]
* Weapon: [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]0%[[/span]]
* Machine: [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]98.5%[[/span]]
* Appliance: [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is improbable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoImprob"]]76%[[/span]]
* Ferrite: [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is improbable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoImprob"]]43%[[/span]]
* Human: [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]0%[[/span]]
* Detonator: [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is improbable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoImprob"]]5%[[/span]]

Based on the above initial results, our assumption that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426 is not a weapon[[/span]] was validated, while additionally allowing for us to conclude that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426 is not a human[[/span]]. This also introduced a new major possibility, that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]SCP-8426 may be an device or appliance[[/span]]. Further ontological analysis has centered around this  [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]potential answer[[/span]].

----

**Associated Adjectives:** To investigate the core issue, namely, what SCP-8426 //does//, analysis was done to identify applicable adjectives and descriptors, to determine what functions SCP-8426 may likely have. The following adjectives are presented, and colored based on reliability:
