Due to the wide range of applicable descriptors, only the most commonly present definitions have been deemed relevant; for example, although SCP-8426 appears to be [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is improbable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoImprob"]]associated with the adjective 'Dangerous'[[/span]], not only is this infrequently true, but it contradicts the fact that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426 is not a weapon[[/span]]. Therefore, we strongly believe that the device is [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]an advanced mechanical device[[/span]], that was [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]created by the Foundation[[/span]], which [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]serves a given, specific purpose[[/span]]. The purpose of SCP-8426 is still variable; however, with this basis, as well as the physical components, the function of SCP-8426 can be [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]further extrapolated[[/span]].
