**Addendum 3:** SCP-8426's Functionality and Purpose

Throughout the investigation into SCP-8426, there has been one common goal: understanding what SCP-8426 was built to do. After gathering the above contextual, component and semantic information, we are now in a place where [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]we can use said observations and assumptions to extrapolate the primary function of SCP-8426[[/span]]. The following is a recreation of the order of operations SCP-8426 takes, upon theoretical activation:

[[div class="blockquote"]]
= [[size 150%]]**SCP-8426 Activation Reconstruction**[[/size]]
-----
+++ Step 1: Loading Material(s)
Due to the fact that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426 is hollow[[/span]] and based on the [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]presence of material loading chamber(s)[[/span]], we suggest that the first step in activation was loading the material chamber(s). Due to the fact that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426 is not a weapon[[/span]], we can assume that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]ammunition is not being loaded[[/span]] into SCP-8426; and given that component analysis suggests that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]SCP-8426 does not create an additional end product[[/span]], we believe that this [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]'material' is the target of SCP-8426's functionality[[/span]].
-----
+++ Step 2: Energy Generation
Given the presence of [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]capacitors, compensated pulsed alternators, and other intake connections[[/span]], the next logical step in the operation of SCP-8426 is to [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]fill the capacitors[[/span]], such that SCP-8426 can be activated. Given the [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]maximum electrical draw of SCP-8426 is 57 megajoules[[/span]], it is clear that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426 was designed to store, and then use significant amounts of energy per activation[[/span]]. It is [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]unclear how long said generation takes[[/span]].
-----
+++ Step 3: Energy Application
Once SCP-8426 has collected enough energy, [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]that energy must be used in the activation[[/span]]. Via adjective comparison and component analysis and the fact that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426's operating chamber has a significant range of operating temperatures[[/span]], we suggest that SCP-8426's primary function is the [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]direct application of said energy to the 'material'[[/span]]. Furthermore, given the [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]continued traits revolving around heat or thermal energy[[/span]], we suggest that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426 applies thermal energy to the 'material'[[/span]] for a [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]given duration of time[[/span]].
-----
+++ Step 4: Ejection
Once SCP-8426 has applied the thermal energy to the 'material', the functionalities and components that remain unused center around [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]the application of force[[/span]], such that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]a directional force is applied to the material[[/span]]. Due to the [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]lack of a dedicated output chamber[[/span]], we believe that the [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]material is ejected from SCP-8426, post-thermal application[[/span]]. Upon ejection, an activation cycle of SCP-8426 is completed.
[[/div]]

We believe that the [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]above reconstruction of SCP-8426's functionality is accurate[[/span]], and therefore, [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is uncertain): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoUncertain"]]we can use this information[[/span]], alongside specific details to narrow down the potential conceptual definition of SCP-8426. Given that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426 is not a weapon[[/span]], we explored [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]non-violent applications using similar functionality[[/span]]: specifically, we were looking for a machine that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]applies heat[[/span]], is [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]useful[[/span]], and is [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]a machine or appliance[[/span]]. We reached the following conclusion:
