**Addendum 4:** Continued Ontological Observation

Following the conclusion of the investigation into SCP-8426, the resultant hypothesis was rejected by both researchers and administrative staff alike; however, replication studies [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]confirmed the initial conclusion[[/span]], and reaffirmed that [[span class="srPre"]](The following statement is probable): [[/span]][[span class="ontoTip ontoProb"]]SCP-8426 is a very expensive toaster[[/span]].

To further confirm this, a Foundation-made AIC webcrawler was tasked with monitoring all video traffic on the internet, identifying recordings with a significant portion of overlapping ontological traits when compared to SCP-8426. Through said comparison, researchers believe that we may gain further clues to the events leading to SCP-8426's conceptual abstraction. Research is ongoing, and any new matches are listed in the table below:
